{"type":"message","id":"e8c1e68d","parentId":"2bc95516","timestamp":"2026-05-14T07:32:10.124Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So Sorftime MCP can read images. They built a Coze workflow for this. Let me think about what they might be asking.\n\nThe user is saying Sorftime's official contact said MCP can read images, and their Coze workflow works. This might be about how Sorftime MCP handles images or product images from 1688/Amazon, etc.\n\nLet me think about what might be relevant here. The user seems to have been discussing Sorftime MCP and CDP browser control. Now they're saying Sorftime's official says MCP can read images.\n\nI'm not 100% sure what they're asking, but since the conversation is about Sorftime MCP, CDP, and reading images, they're probably following up on the previous discussion. They might be saying we don't need CDP since Sorftime MCP can already read images.\n\nWait, but Sorftime MCP is an API-based service for Amazon data. The question is about reading images. Coze workflow might process images differently.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. Sorftime MCP is Amazon product data API. It can pull product info, reviews, etc. \n\nThe user is saying Sorftime's official people said \"MCP可以读取到图片\" (MCP can read images). They built a Coze workflow for it. So the point seems to be that maybe we don't need CDP browser control since Sorftime MCP already supports reading images from product pages.\n\nBut Sorftime MCP is Amazon-specific. For other sources like 1688 product images, it might not work.\n\nI'm not sure what they want me to respond to here. They might be:\n1. Asking me to check/verify this\n2. Making a point that we should use Sorftime MCP instead of CDP\n3. Asking if Sorftime can replace CDP for image reading\n\nI should ask for clarification since this is a fairly vague follow-up message. But actually, reading the context more carefully - they seem to be telling me that Sorftime's official confirmed their MCP can read images, and they have a working Coze workflow for it.\n\n\nI should probably check whether Sorftime MCP can actually handle images in our current setup, and if so, whether that affects our approach to this problem.","thinkingSignature":"c4e68817329da0472222a8335d9c37173d9d65c6ba002897d6f41609355c0ffb"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n好的，Sorftime 官方确认 MCP 可以读取图片，并且他们自己搭建的 Coze 工作流已经跑通了。\n\n这说明 Sorftime MCP 本身是支持图片的，你不用自己折腾 CDP 了。\n\n不过我想确认一下——你现在是想让我帮你做什么？比如：\n1. **在我们的 Coze 工作流里接入 Sorftime MCP** 读取产品图片？\n2. **还是确认 Sorftime MCP 能读到哪些图片**（1688？Amazon？）？\n3. **还是你在复盘之前那个思路，说我们可以直接用 Sorftime MCP 替代 CDP**？\n\n告诉我你下一步想往哪个方向推，我来配合你。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2962,"output":573,"cacheRead":20512,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24047,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778743908089,"responseId":"0654ad6807bee72d6f617d9b69c1d0b7"}}
