{"type":"message","id":"60ee8c88","parentId":"5ad62d4b","timestamp":"2026-05-14T07:33:47.050Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is expressing frustration that after all this time, nothing is working in production. Let me understand the current situation:\n\n1. They've been trying to set up Sorftime MCP to read product images\n2. They contacted Sorftime official and they said MCP can read images, and their Coze workflow setup works\n3. The user is frustrated that nothing is in production yet\n\nLet me check the current state of things - what's been attempted, what failed, and what the path forward should be. I need to look at recent memory and understand the current blocker.\n\nKey points from what I've read:\n- Sorftime MCP was set up and can call TikTok APIs\n- 50 records were written to a Feishu table\n\n\n- The core problem is that Sorftime returns only product IDs without images, so the user proposed using TikTok product preview URLs to construct image URLs by swapping the ID into a template they provided\n- This requires accessing TikTok through either a proxy or browser, but there's no VPN available and the browser setup isn't working yet due to device identity requirements\n- Sorftime officially confirmed their MCP can read images, which suggests the Coze workflow might handle image retrieval differently than the current approach\n","thinkingSignature":"a3ab2312ca1d24700515d46ad1d57895ce71b63ab4d554959ea5113cd5dbe125"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tl77gqc8j37u_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw status 2>&1 | head -50"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2856,"output":279,"cacheRead":26656,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29791,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778744009693,"responseId":"0654adc92f3524bd9365b649236d59a8"}}
