{"type":"message","id":"e3187ad2","parentId":"9c3fee67","timestamp":"2026-05-14T07:34:07.529Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is frustrated because we haven't made real progress toward a production workflow despite a lot of back-and-forth. Let me understand the current situation:\n\n1. We've been trying to connect Sorftime MCP for TikTok data\n2. We've been trying to get browser access to TikTok to capture product images\n3. The key issue from today: Sorftime MCP says they CAN read images via their Coze workflow\n4. The user's frustration is valid - we haven't gone live with any real production pipeline\n\nLet me check the current state of things more carefully. I need to check if there's a working Coze workflow or if Sorftime MCP has some image capability I haven't fully explored. Let me check what tools we actually have available with Sorftime MCP.\n\n\nThe user mentioned that Sorftime's official team confirmed their MCP can read images - they even demonstrated it working through a Coze workflow they set up. This suggests their solution might already have image capabilities built in, so I should investigate what we're actually working with rather than assuming we need to find a workaround.","thinkingSignature":"32e140c5b97d6aebf02f4c1134d7964af489790c7fba560419c4b16931e4ec0e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ieddw7tfeftf_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"crisp-sage","timeout":5000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":87,"output":263,"cacheRead":29504,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29854,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778744037160,"responseId":"0654ade590f7a574b6ce343af0653e82"}}
