{"type":"message","id":"251887f9","parentId":"ef61e55a","timestamp":"2026-05-14T07:35:22.797Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying that the browser/CDP approach has low success rate. They're right - the browser approach for TTS product scraping is unreliable and hasn't been working properly due to the device identity issue.\n\nLet me think about what the user is really frustrated about:\n1. We've spent a long time trying to get things working\n2. The browser/CDP approach (canvas) is unreliable\n3. Sorftime MCP can read images (according to the official person they contacted)\n4. They want to get to production\n\nThe core issue is that Sorftime MCP doesn't return product images in its API responses - it only returns product IDs. The user's idea was:\n- Take the product ID\n- Construct a TikTok product URL (the `encode_params` seems to be fixed)\n\n\n- Use the browser to access the URL and get the main image\n\nBut the browser tool isn't working due to device identity issues. The user is frustrated we've been stuck on this for so long.\n\nThe key insight from the Sorftime official is that their MCP can read images and their Coze workflow works, which suggests the issue might be with how we're using the MCP rather than the tool itself. So instead of relying on the browser approach, maybe we're missing something about how Sorftime MCP is actually supposed to work.\n\nThe user has confirmed their Coze workflow can access TikTok product URLs directly and extract images, so the problem isn't network access—it's that we haven't properly set up the MCP integration yet. We need to figure out how to properly use Sorftime MCP to get product images directly rather than trying to construct URLs and scrape them manually.\n\nI should be honest about the browser/CDP approach being unreliable and suggest we pivot to understanding how Sorftime MCP's image reading actually works in their Coze workflow, then apply that same logic to our setup.","thinkingSignature":"06371111a1f298287105fbc7e2b03f07c2b93a1c346efd669d55e4579241ec34"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n对，你说得很准。\n\nCDP 浏览器这条路本身就不稳——登录态维护、页面结构变化、验证码、浏览器崩溃...成功率低、维护成本高，之前折腾了很久也没跑通。\n\n---\n\n**现在重新看 Sorftime 官方说\"MCP 可以读取图片，Coze 工作流可以\"——这是个重要信号。**\n\nSorftime MCP 本身能读图片，意味着：\n- 他们的 MCP 服务端做了截图/图片提取逻辑\n- Coze 工作流调用 MCP 时拿到的不是纯文本 ID，而是图片数据\n\n**问题是我们之前只调用了 Sorftime 的文字接口，没触发图片读取能力。**\n\n---\n\n## 你的想法是...\n\n既然 Sorftime MCP 官方说能读图片，我们是不是应该：\n1. **直接问 Sorftime 官方**：他们的 MCP 工具哪个能返回图片？调用方式是什么？\n2. **让他们给你看看 Coze 工作流怎么配置的**——抄过来\n\n这样不用我们自己折腾 CDP，Sorftime 那边已经验证过能跑通。\n\n你觉得呢？还是你有其他的思路？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":167,"output":582,"cacheRead":29856,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30605,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778744082576,"responseId":"0654ae121558382b71789395b1a07e43"}}
