{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"user:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b6f63b7cae8acc43e55ded1db07b\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-05-14 15:53 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"c25e8e96","parentId":"46d2502b","timestamp":"2026-05-14T07:53:57.373Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"9dad3d32","parentId":"c25e8e96","timestamp":"2026-05-14T07:54:19.625Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying they checked and confirmed that Sorftime MCP doesn't return images. So the approach of using Sorftime MCP directly for images won't work. \n\nWe need another approach. The user's original idea was:\n1. Use Sorftime to get the ProductId\n2. Construct a TikTok product URL by replacing the ID in a template URL\n3. Use the browser to access the URL and get the main image\n\nBut the browser tool isn't working due to device identity issues. And CDP approach has low success rate.\n\nWhat are our options now?\n1. Wait for Sorftime key to be recharged\n2. Try EchoTik API instead\n3. Use a different approach for images\n\nThe user seems frustrated. Let me think about what else could work...\n\nActually, wait - the user said \"反回不了图片\" - confirming it doesn't return images. They might be looking for confirmation or next steps.\n\nThe key issue is:\n- Sorftime MCP doesn't return images (confirmed)\n- The browser approach (CDP) has problems - not working due to device identity, low success rate even when it works\n- The key is expired\n\nMaybe the Coze workflow approach the Sorftime people use works differently? Or maybe we need to try a different image approach.\n\nLet me ask about what they want to do next. Or maybe I should think about alternative approaches.\n\nActually, thinking about this more practically - what if we don't need to scrape images at all? What if we use the TikTok product URL and let the user view the product in their own browser? The image is mainly for the user to evaluate the product visually. \n\nBut for the workflow to be truly automated, we do need the images in the spreadsheet.\n\nAnother thought: could we use a different image source? Like 1688 image search based on the product title? Or use the product title to search on Google Images?\n\nOr maybe the simplest approach: when we write to the spreadsheet, we include the TikTok product URL as a link, and the user can click through to see the product images. Not ideal, but it avoids the image scraping problem entirely.\n\n\nThe user has confirmed Sorftime MCP doesn't return images, so browser scraping is our only option—and that's been problematic with device identity issues. I'm considering whether we should include product links directly in the spreadsheet instead, or explore alternative image sources like reverse image searches, but I should clarify what direction they want to take before proposing solutions.","thinkingSignature":"13f5114b34656a2b69ed0b7df4fc0436ec1f3e6a467d1fc377c0578d95297a32"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n明白了，Sorftime MCP **本身不返回图片**，他们的 Coze 工作流估计也是用浏览器额外抓的截图。\n\n那我们现在图片这块真的没路了——\n\n- ❌ Sorftime API 不返回图片\n- ❌ CDP 浏览器方案不稳定/进不来\n- ❌ `web_fetch` 被墙\n\n---\n\n**唯一现实的路**：等你充值后，用你之前说的 **ID 替换 + TikTok URL** 方案——Sorftime 拿 ProductId → 拼 URL → 浏览器打开 → 截图进表格。\n\n但这需要浏览器能跑起来。你说你的 Ubuntu 有 Chrome，网络能翻墙——\n\n我现在能直接用你的 `openclaw browser` 吗？你本地有没有装 `openclaw` 桌面客户端？或者你是用服务器版本的？\n\n如果浏览器跑不起来，这条路也堵死了。\n\n---\n\n**你真正想要的是什么？** 是把图片自动写入飞书表格，还是有个可视化的产品列表就行？如果只是看产品数据，其实 **TikTok 产品链接 + 标题 + 价格 + 销量** 进表格也能用，不一定要图片。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":37422,"output":719,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38141,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778745237394,"responseId":"0654b295e808e36ec63236b22acef71c"}}
